if you've a mind to ♪

02:49.266 --> 02:51.333
♪ You can't take a shower
in a parakeet cage ♪

02:51.366 --> 02:53.433
♪ You can't take
a shower in a parakeet cage ♪

02:53.466 --> 02:55.033
♪ You can't take a shower ♪

02:55.066 --> 02:56.700
(faintly):
♪ In a parakeet cage ♪

02:56.733 --> 02:59.500
♪ But you can be happy
if you've a mind to ♪

02:59.533 --> 03:01.733
♪ All you got to do
is put your mind to it ♪

03:01.766 --> 03:04.666
♪ Knuckle down, buckle down,
do it, do it, do it ♪

03:04.700 --> 03:07.233
♪ Well, you can't go a‐swimming
in a baseball pool ♪

03:07.266 --> 03:10.100
♪ You can't go swimming in
a baseball pool ♪

03:10.133 --> 03:12.466
♪ You can't go swimming
in a baseball pool ♪

03:12.500 --> 03:15.666
♪ But you can be happy
if you've a mind to... ♪

03:15.700 --> 03:19.166
(toilet flushes)

03:19.200 --> 03:20.333
(chuckles)

03:20.366 --> 03:23.033
Let me see that lipstick.

03:27.666 --> 03:30.500
♪ You can't change film
with a kid on your back ♪

03:30.533 --> 03:33.200
♪ You can't change film with
a kid on your back ♪

03:33.233 --> 03:35.566
♪ You can't change film
with a kid on your back ♪

03:35.600 --> 03:37.700
♪ But you can be happy
if you've a mind to ♪

03:37.733 --> 03:39.100
(clears throat)

03:39.133 --> 03:41.100
♪ With a tiger in your car ♪

03:41.133 --> 03:43.166
♪ You can't drive around
with a tiger in your car... ♪

03:43.200 --> 03:46.033
(laughs softly)

03:46.066 --> 03:47.366
(whispers):
I like your getup.

03:47.400 --> 03:49.233
‐(laughs)
‐Thank you.

03:49.266 --> 03:50.800
♪ All you got to do... ♪

03:50.833 --> 03:53.533
‐(toilet flushes)
‐(music playing)

04:00.366 --> 04:03.600
We need a boiler
and some duds for you.

04:03.633 --> 04:05.166
And maybe requisition a bottle

04:05.200 --> 04:08.533
of certified non‐toilet hooch
in reward.

04:08.566 --> 04:11.800
Hey. Stay clean, stay free.

04:11.833 --> 04:13.533
Unless you broke out
just to go back.

04:14.733 --> 04:17.233
Now whiplash those duds.

04:20.399 --> 04:22.533
Which of you ladies wants
to go around the world

04:22.566 --> 04:24.700
with this big buck, huh?

04:26.733 --> 04:29.466
I'll take a ride.

04:29.500 --> 04:31.566
(insects chirping)

04:31.600 --> 04:33.600
(pounding on door)

04:36.766 --> 04:38.566
THURMAN:
What the heck?

04:38.600 --> 04:40.600
(footsteps)

04:45.233 --> 04:47.400
(door opens)

04:47.433 --> 04:49.600
ZELMARE:
Happy holiday.

04:49.633 --> 04:50.766
(laughs)

04:50.800 --> 04:52.466
THURMAN:
D‐Dibrell?

04:52.500 --> 04:54.033
Get down here.

04:54.066 --> 04:56.033
It's your sister, the elder,

04:56.066 --> 04:59.300
and she's, she's brought
a friend.

05:00.766 --> 05:02.500
(whispers):
Back to bed.

05:04.633 --> 05:07.100
(sighs)

05:09.100 --> 05:12.066
(Dibrell and Zelmare exclaiming)

05:12.100 --> 05:13.333
ZELMARE:
What?!

05:13.366 --> 05:15.366
(laughter)

05:17.766 --> 05:19.766
(Zelmare crying)

05:21.266 --> 05:23.233
DIBRELL:
What are you doing here?

05:23.266 --> 05:25.100
Showing up, middle of night.

05:25.133 --> 05:28.800
This is a decent house
with decent people.

05:28.833 --> 05:30.700
‐Yeah. Yeah.
‐Would've called, missus,

05:30.733 --> 05:33.700
but we found ourselves
without precise coinery.

05:33.733 --> 05:35.533
She ain't mad.
Just bossy, like always.

05:35.566 --> 05:37.533
I ain't neither.

05:37.566 --> 05:40.400
And just what kind of Halloween
costumes you got on?

05:40.433 --> 05:42.066
ZELMARE:
Wasn't released
but this morning.

05:42.100 --> 05:43.733
SWANEE:
No time to shop proper.

05:43.766 --> 05:45.633
But I feel I come across rugged.

05:45.666 --> 05:47.700
Hon, let's not keep them
crowded in the doorway.

05:47.733 --> 05:49.366
‐Come on in. You hungry?
‐(laughs)

05:49.400 --> 05:53.266
‐Famished.
‐DIBRELL: Uh, they can't
stay here.

05:53.300 --> 05:55.300
You can't stay here.

05:55.333 --> 05:58.200
Well, a cup of coffee, at least.
She's your sister.

06:00.466 --> 06:02.466
‐Come on.
‐Yeah.
‐(floorboard creaks)

06:04.400 --> 06:05.466
Well, look at you.

06:05.500 --> 06:07.533
Little Miss All Grown‐up.

06:07.566 --> 06:09.400
(laughs) Come down here
and give your auntie a hug!

06:09.433 --> 06:12.633
(laughs)
Ooh!

06:12.666 --> 06:15.600
Whoa! No, there...

06:15.633 --> 06:18.600
Don't get ideas.
She's a good girl.

06:18.633 --> 06:22.100
Oh...
(exclaims)

06:22.133 --> 06:24.566
Am I the only one
who smells dead people?

06:27.466 --> 06:30.400
(laughs)

06:35.633 --> 06:37.400
In the stir,
the eggs is powdered.

06:37.433 --> 06:40.766
Eggs are powdered. Speak proper.

06:40.800 --> 06:43.266
Taken her education upon myself.

06:43.300 --> 06:45.300
SWANEE:
You'd have thunk the white
school they shipped me to

06:45.333 --> 06:47.133
from the reservation
would've seen to my English,

06:47.166 --> 06:49.666
but they was mostly concerned
with raping the native

06:49.700 --> 06:51.700
‐out of me.
‐Language.

06:52.800 --> 06:55.766
Sorry. Did I say that wrong?

06:55.800 --> 06:58.066
Looks like you done well
for yourself

06:58.100 --> 06:59.600
these years I've been away.

06:59.633 --> 07:01.333
‐You ain't getting no handout.
‐Listen at you,

07:01.366 --> 07:03.366
acting like the big sister.

07:03.400 --> 07:05.033
Wasn't asking for money.

07:05.066 --> 07:06.600
Swanee and me got prospects.

07:06.633 --> 07:08.466
What kind of prospects?

07:09.833 --> 07:13.100
Bank robbing.
(exhales sharply)

07:13.133 --> 07:14.166
Go to your room.

07:14.200 --> 07:15.400
Now.

07:16.433 --> 07:17.700
Mind your mama.

07:17.733 --> 07:19.733
We catch up tomorrow.

07:30.700 --> 07:34.333
DIBRELL:
They didn't let you go
from that prison, did they?

07:34.366 --> 07:37.366
You crushed out.

07:37.400 --> 07:39.600
We freed ourselves
on our own recognizance.

07:39.633 --> 07:42.300
What happened was, we met a moll

07:42.333 --> 07:45.733
goes with one of them Cannon
boys, knew I was your sister.

07:45.766 --> 07:48.733
She tells me you in the hole
to some big‐time leg‐breakers,

07:48.766 --> 07:50.500
who knows why.

07:50.533 --> 07:53.366
So we decided
to come bail you out.

07:53.400 --> 07:55.700
Leg‐breakers if you're lucky.

07:55.733 --> 07:59.233
‐Nothing to say?
‐Don't need your help.

07:59.266 --> 08:01.466
Got everything under control.

08:01.500 --> 08:03.400
How much interest he charging?

08:03.433 --> 08:06.533
Ten percent the first month,
then it goes up from there.

08:06.566 --> 08:08.400
Don't tell her that.

08:08.433 --> 08:11.066
I told you. Didn't I say?

08:11.100 --> 08:12.500
Day one,

08:12.533 --> 08:14.700
we shouldn't have
taken that loan.

08:14.733 --> 08:16.366
DIBRELL:
That or go under. Then what?

08:16.400 --> 08:19.000
This is our problem...

08:23.833 --> 08:27.033
HARVARD:
As I said in my letter,
Mrs. Will,

08:27.066 --> 08:31.566
a cancer ward will be de rigueur
in any modern hospital.

08:31.600 --> 08:35.066
They have an entire wing
up at the Mayo Clinic.

08:35.100 --> 08:38.066
And I would hazard
that our Missouri elite deserve

08:38.100 --> 08:41.666
the same quality care
as the rubes up in Minnesota.

08:41.700 --> 08:43.666
Don't you think?

08:43.700 --> 08:46.533
Say the number.

08:49.100 --> 08:51.100
(engine idling)

08:55.600 --> 08:59.033
HARVARD:
And unless you object,

08:59.066 --> 09:02.566
the plaque will read "The Walter
and Mathilda Will Cancer Ward."

09:02.600 --> 09:04.733
MATHILDA:
Fine. Just promise me, no Jews.

09:04.766 --> 09:06.500
(laughs)
No Jews...

09:06.533 --> 09:08.100
‐(gunfire)
‐Oh!

09:08.133 --> 09:10.133
(screaming)

09:12.600 --> 09:15.066
(tires screeching)

09:15.100 --> 09:16.700
‐You get him?
‐I‐I think so.

09:16.733 --> 09:18.733
Think...?
What do you mean, "think so"?

09:37.466 --> 09:39.466
(dog barking in distance)

09:55.133 --> 09:57.133
(man whistles)

10:03.600 --> 10:06.100
What's the skinny?

10:06.133 --> 10:08.333
You know. Salad days.

10:15.400 --> 10:18.233
I got that formaldehyde
your dad asked for.

10:18.266 --> 10:19.766
It's inside.

10:19.800 --> 10:21.600
We got a big one today.

10:21.633 --> 10:25.033
Italians, with all the wailing
and the rending of clothes.

10:25.066 --> 10:27.033
You'd better wait here.

10:27.066 --> 10:29.700
They're not too big
on colored folks.

10:29.733 --> 10:31.233
No offense.

10:31.266 --> 10:34.200
(sighs)

10:34.233 --> 10:36.233
(organ music playing)

10:47.266 --> 10:49.266
(crying in distance)

10:52.166 --> 10:54.166
‐(crying)
‐(guests murmuring)

11:14.800 --> 11:16.133
(door opens)

11:23.533 --> 11:25.533
(guests murmuring)

11:46.666 --> 11:48.666
(whispering indistinctly)

12:09.633 --> 12:11.300
ORAETTA:
Shouldn't be doing that.

12:15.133 --> 12:17.233
Well, now, look at you.

12:17.266 --> 12:20.700
Like a lucky penny,
always turning up.

12:20.733 --> 12:22.233
A bad penny.

12:22.266 --> 12:25.266
Bad pennies turn up.

12:26.300 --> 12:28.600
And what do lucky pennies do?

12:28.633 --> 12:30.600
Bring good luck.

12:30.633 --> 12:32.366
(chuckles)

12:36.066 --> 12:37.666
‐Well.
‐(door closes)

12:37.700 --> 12:41.466
And she speaks French.

12:41.500 --> 12:44.500
Yes, she does.

12:48.666 --> 12:50.300
Asshole.

12:50.333 --> 12:52.166
Either you got him
or you didn't.

12:52.200 --> 12:53.766
I‐I think so.

12:53.800 --> 12:57.066
‐We definitely got a driver.
‐What driver? Whose driver?

12:59.066 --> 13:01.066
‐I know you?
‐Mr. Fadda,

13:01.100 --> 13:04.566
Oraetta Mayflower
from St. Bartholomew's.

13:04.600 --> 13:06.700
Condolences for your loss.

13:06.733 --> 13:10.166
‐You're the nurse. His nurse.
‐Yes, sir.

13:10.200 --> 13:12.200
I was with your father
when he passed.

13:13.600 --> 13:15.633
But I want you to know
it was real peaceful.

13:15.666 --> 13:17.333
Like a baby going to sleep.

13:17.366 --> 13:20.300
That's‐‐ Don't do that.

13:20.333 --> 13:22.066
Andiamo.

13:22.100 --> 13:23.733
‐Let's go.
‐Andiamo...

13:23.766 --> 13:25.100
Thank you.

13:25.133 --> 13:26.466
‐You're gonna go back.
‐Boss.

13:26.500 --> 13:28.333
No.

13:28.366 --> 13:31.566
This fucking sfigato doesn't
get to breathe air

13:31.600 --> 13:33.133
while some people...

13:34.733 --> 13:38.133
...some people, better people,
are buried in the ground.

13:38.166 --> 13:40.233
They ain't buried him yet.

13:40.266 --> 13:44.200
Shut the fuck up.

13:47.133 --> 13:49.733
What's the matter? They didn't
let you talk on the boat over?

13:49.766 --> 13:51.600
You got to bust my balls now?
At Pop's funeral?

13:51.633 --> 13:53.600
CHIANNA:
Boys. Don't fight.

13:53.633 --> 13:55.466
Already my heart breaks.

13:55.500 --> 13:57.433
Don't worry, Ma,
we're just playing.

13:57.466 --> 13:59.366
‐Just boys playing.
‐And the ring.

13:59.400 --> 14:01.400
Your father's ring. Il mignolo.

14:01.433 --> 14:03.300
‐What about his ring?
‐You couldn't wait

14:03.333 --> 14:06.166
until he was cold
before you take him apart?

14:06.200 --> 14:08.166
‐Your own father.
‐What are you talking
about, Mama?

14:08.200 --> 14:10.066
Nobody took anything.

14:41.266 --> 14:45.300
Ah, and the business was
really good.

15:14.266 --> 15:16.266
Look.

15:20.733 --> 15:22.700
I keep his teeth in my pocket.

15:22.733 --> 15:25.100
Look.

15:26.466 --> 15:29.033
Look.

15:31.333 --> 15:33.633
To remind me...

15:33.666 --> 15:37.733
business, family, country.

15:37.766 --> 15:41.466
Business,
family, country.

15:52.333 --> 15:54.400
No.

15:54.433 --> 15:56.600
The question is:

15:56.633 --> 16:00.033
which side are you on now...

16:00.066 --> 16:02.066
kid?

16:07.566 --> 16:09.766
You take the next one.

16:09.800 --> 16:11.400
(speaks Italian)

16:17.800 --> 16:20.300
(car door closes)

16:20.333 --> 16:22.433
(engine starts)

16:22.466 --> 16:24.466
(car doors closing)

16:30.333 --> 16:32.333
(engine starts)

16:37.466 --> 16:39.466
(indistinct chatter)

16:41.533 --> 16:43.533
♪ ♪

16:51.833 --> 16:54.033
(indistinct radio transmission)

16:57.766 --> 17:01.200
(whispering):
One little, two little,
three little Indians.

17:01.233 --> 17:04.133
Four little, five little,
six little Indians.

17:07.532 --> 17:10.566
♪ One little ♪

17:10.599 --> 17:12.599
♪ Two little ♪

17:12.633 --> 17:15.333
♪ Three little Indians ♪

17:17.366 --> 17:22.032
♪ Four little, five little ♪

17:23.333 --> 17:25.333
♪ Five little. ♪

17:26.633 --> 17:27.800
One little, two little...

17:27.833 --> 17:30.600
(muttering)

17:30.633 --> 17:33.500
HARVARD:
I know what I saw,
what this is.

17:33.533 --> 17:35.333
And that is?

17:35.366 --> 17:39.466
Retribution for some
perceived slight.

17:39.500 --> 17:41.666
‐Against Mrs. Will?
‐No.

17:41.700 --> 17:43.766
Against me.

17:43.800 --> 17:45.133
Enough already!

17:45.166 --> 17:46.700
Sir, you should take
a restorative.

17:46.733 --> 17:48.300
Something for your nerves.

17:48.333 --> 17:50.066
Your blood pressure is
very high.

17:50.100 --> 17:52.200
Do you hear that?
I'm hypertensive.

17:52.233 --> 17:55.200
If I have a stroke, promise me
you'll charge them with murder.

17:56.633 --> 17:58.300
Charge who?

17:58.333 --> 18:00.633
The hatchet men.

18:00.666 --> 18:04.033
Uh, sir... you're not making
a lot of sense.

18:04.066 --> 18:05.533
Y‐You said it was a blue Ford.

18:05.566 --> 18:10.133
We had, five days ago,
in this hospital, a fracas.

18:10.166 --> 18:12.300
An incursion of undesirables.

18:12.333 --> 18:16.300
Men of‐‐ and I'm no bigot‐‐
but Italian origin,

18:16.333 --> 18:18.366
‐who I turned away.
‐Mm.

18:18.400 --> 18:21.433
And you think this is related?

18:21.466 --> 18:23.433
Son, are you deaf?

18:23.466 --> 18:25.633
We're talking
a gunshot wound scenario,

18:25.666 --> 18:28.566
combined with a half dozen
swarthy lotharios

18:28.600 --> 18:31.433
straight out of central casting,
and me,

18:31.466 --> 18:34.266
a law‐abiding citizen
of Protestant descent

18:34.300 --> 18:36.566
enforcing the rules
of this establishment,

18:36.600 --> 18:39.200
maintaining the purity
of our blood supply.

18:39.233 --> 18:42.366
Dr. Harvard, I'm gonna put you
with our sketchbook artist.

18:42.400 --> 18:44.700
See if you can reconstruct
the visage of some of these‐‐

18:44.733 --> 18:47.533
what did you call them‐‐
lotharios?

18:47.566 --> 18:50.300
I'm gonna make sure to issue
a full‐point bulletin

18:50.333 --> 18:52.533
for this blue Ford,
license plates unknown.

18:52.566 --> 18:57.100
But... it would help
if you could say for certain

18:57.133 --> 19:00.300
that the man you saw
with the gun was the same

19:00.333 --> 19:02.566
as the man or men you removed
from the premises

19:02.600 --> 19:04.566
a, a few days bygone.

19:04.600 --> 19:06.633
I saw...

19:06.666 --> 19:08.033
(sighs)

19:08.066 --> 19:12.466
I'll be honest,
I only saw the gun.

19:12.500 --> 19:17.433
Well, yes, sir,
they can be... arresting.

19:17.466 --> 19:20.600
Do you think‐‐
should I increase security

19:20.633 --> 19:22.566
‐in case they...?
‐We'll get back to you.

19:22.600 --> 19:24.666
(knocking and grunting
rhythmically)

19:24.700 --> 19:27.366
It's... no, no,

19:27.400 --> 19:29.433
you don't have to...
Just turn the knob.

19:29.466 --> 19:32.033
(continues knocking
and grunting)

19:32.066 --> 19:33.633
Is he some kind of retard?

19:37.766 --> 19:39.533
Thank you for your cooperation.

19:39.566 --> 19:41.300
You'll be hearing
from me shortly.

20:02.100 --> 20:05.033
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

20:05.066 --> 20:08.800
♪ The Funky Dawgz Brass Band,
y'all ♪

20:08.833 --> 20:11.433
♪ You know we're number one,
turn it up, y'all ♪

20:14.133 --> 20:16.366
♪ You know what we do,
you know our résumé... ♪

20:19.733 --> 20:21.333
LOY:
Let's go.

20:21.366 --> 20:23.366
♪ ♪

20:44.533 --> 20:46.333
Listen to me.

20:48.266 --> 20:52.133
I'm not your father,
but I'm responsible for you.

20:52.166 --> 20:56.266
These people inside,
they're your blood.

20:56.300 --> 21:00.433
But do they love you?
Do they respect you?

21:00.466 --> 21:03.333
You know how you know?

21:03.366 --> 21:05.666
They get down on your level,

21:05.700 --> 21:08.800
they look you in the eye.

21:08.833 --> 21:12.333
That's when you know you're not
just along for the ride.

21:12.366 --> 21:14.066
Capisce?

21:14.100 --> 21:15.300
Capisco.

21:15.333 --> 21:18.000
(chuckles)
Capisco.

21:32.200 --> 21:35.766
He comes in, you cop a squat.

21:37.366 --> 21:39.300
Send out my boy first.

21:39.333 --> 21:43.133
What's the matter,
you don't trust me?

21:55.800 --> 21:59.000
(speaking Italian)

22:03.533 --> 22:05.633
Do you remember me?
Gaetano. Hey.

22:05.666 --> 22:08.066
That's close enough.

22:14.133 --> 22:16.400
You know who I am?

22:16.433 --> 22:19.366
Yeah. You're the guy that's
not coming any closer,

22:19.400 --> 22:20.566
or I'll pop you one.

22:25.400 --> 22:29.066
He says he's gonna
punch you in the face.

22:32.166 --> 22:34.400
He really say that?

22:34.433 --> 22:36.133
Yeah.

22:36.166 --> 22:37.700
(laughing)

22:44.433 --> 22:49.266
Stop! Stop.

22:49.300 --> 22:52.000
Gaetano...

23:05.366 --> 23:07.333
Are we good?

23:07.366 --> 23:09.166
You tell me.

23:09.200 --> 23:12.033
Yeah, we're good.

23:12.066 --> 23:14.633
Your mama's inside.
Go give her a kiss.

23:23.700 --> 23:25.033
Stai bene?

23:30.700 --> 23:32.400
I'll give you a minute
with your boy.

23:32.433 --> 23:35.100
We should sit sometime,
you and me.

23:35.133 --> 23:39.100
Hash out the rumpus.
Things have changed.

23:40.100 --> 23:42.566
Nothing's changed.

23:42.600 --> 23:45.200
Have a nice visit.

23:48.233 --> 23:51.066
Come here.

24:00.433 --> 24:04.600
